Package: scholarAnalyzer
Title: Google Scholar Citation Analyzer with Self-Citation Detection
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Your", "Name", email = "your.email@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A Shiny application that fetches publication data from Google Scholar
    and detects self-citations by cross-referencing with the Semantic Scholar API.
    Citation counts use Google Scholar as the authoritative source. Self-citations
    are identified when any co-author of the original paper also appears as an
    author of a citing paper. Adjusted citation counts are computed by subtracting
    detected self-citations from the Google Scholar total.
